node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by kirstin™ on July 23, 2021 tagging @jenkosta. May be an image of 2 people.

node.text:
It’s really hard to put my thoughts in to words… I almost didn’t want to make a post because I’m still trying to process it all. I’ve never felt so shocked and devastated … and knowing I won’t get your silly videos or hear your laugh breaks my heart. I immediately went back through all our chats, our photos… I can’t find them all on my phone but I can SEE them … Halloween, 4th of July, being roomies, weho, just chillin… You were there in my darkest times with hugs and laughter. You supported me when I could barely afford to sleep on your couch and let me borrow your sweet Lucy to cuddle when I was down because pups just make everything better!! Always there when I was sad or struggling. You were such an incredible friend to sooo many people and way too selfless with your love and kindness. The best dog mom. The most supportive and FUNNIEST friend. I’m so so sorry if I ever took it for granted. 

I remember when I first met you. I was in awe of you. I felt drawn to your kindness and fuck you are so funny. And you took me under your wing. All our Broadway talks and chasing our dreams… SO much laughter. You were so so loved and brought light to everyone you met. You were the best, @jenkosta 🥺💔 So many things I wish I had said or done. If I could go back I’d do anything. 

Thank you for my Olaf. My forever bestie. My forever protector. He will miss his godmother. 🥺 Thank you for going to BLM protests w me, thank you for always making time, thank you for your effort, your love. Everything. Looking back thank you for everything. Now Lucy is truly in the sky with diamonds, because you were always my gem 💎 I hope y’all are snuggling and eating soft serve together. I’m so sorry I didn’t let you know how much you mean to me ❤️‍🩹 I love you so fucking much. Nothing feels right these words don’t even feel right. But I love you so much 💎✨

node.text:
My first little is turning lucky 7 today. 7 years he has been my best friend and protector. Is it embarrassing to cry when compiling photos just because that’s how much we’ve been through 🥲🥲🥲
I love this dog more than anything in the world. 🥺
Happy Birthday, sweet Olaf! I am forever holding on tight to you ❣️
